commit_message: Comment out downloading of histone methylation data.
Update workflow to use full dataset.
Make window size around TSS/TES a Kepler parameter.
Make small changes to polish pipeline for submission to Mark.
Fix MEME error inexplicably created by Kepler.

Wrap external execution actors in composites.

Make each external execution actor take relevant parameters by wrapping it in a
composite actor.
Delinearize workflow, so that rather than making each actor execute after the
last, each actor instead has clear dependencies on data emitted by other
actors.
Add Mark's modifications from Friday meeting.
Integrate location analysis, gene ontology, and pathway analysis into workflow.
Add script to extract gene names from annotated GFF file.
Properly parse separate group fields in GFF3 files.
Fix error when comment line encountered.
Break peak stats actors into subworkflow.
Replace annotate-genes.R with simpler annotate-peaks.R for peak annotation.
Tweak output filename and column names.
Add script to perform pathway analysis.
Add column name to GO output.
Add script for producing simplified GO output.
Write modular replacement for annotate-genes.R that does only annotation.
Take strandedness into account when doing location analysis.
Handle peaks whose seqnames are not in reference set.
Revert changes inadvertently committed in f72e493e2584dc08e2131f5bf8c22b2b49703b9c.
Allow proximal TSS/TES boundaries to be defined on command line.
Add proper frame and group columns to GFF file.
Add R script to write human TSS file.
Only get GO info for peaks in proximal promoter.

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:jwintersinger/chipseq-workflow

Add feature location (TSS or geneEnd) as parameter to annotate_peaks().
Permit changing annotation DB and reference assembly in Kepler.
Add gene symbol names and GO information.
Add note regarding obsolute nature to histone pipeline.
Calculate peak stats and draw histograms.
Add script to extract GFF fields of interest.
Add workflows in approximate state when submitted to Bieda.
